      "Process_Info": {
        "Process_Category": "Additive Manufacturing - Electron Beam Melting",
        "Process_Text": {
          "original": "The EBM specimens were fabricated using an Arcam A2X EBM system (Arcam AB, Molndal, Sweden). The precursor powder of the Ti-48Al-2Cr-2Nb alloy, used in the present study, consists of spherical particles of which average diameter is around 100 μm. An electron beam was scanned according to a zigzag pattern; the building path was rotated by 90° between each layer. The cylindrical bars of Ti-48Al-2Cr-2Nb alloy were fabricated by EBM operated at 60 kV. The layer thickness for each fed powder layer was 90 μm and the pre-heating temperature before melting powder layer was 1060°C. The angle (θ) between the building direction and cylindrical axis of these rods was set to 0°, 45° and 90°, as shown in Fig. 1.",
          "simplified": "EBM using Arcam A2X system, 60 kV, layer thickness 90 μm, pre-heating 1060°C, zigzag scan with 90° rotation between layers. Building direction angles: 0°, 45°, 90°."
        },
        "Equipment": "Arcam A2X EBM system",
        "Key_Params": {
          "Voltage_kV": 60,
          "Layer_Thickness_um": 90,
          "Preheating_Temperature_K": 1333.15,
          "Building_Angle_deg": 0
        }
      },
      "Microstructure_Info": {
        "Microstructure_Text": {
          "original": "The microstructure is composed of the repeated stack of two layers with different characteristic features. One is predominantly composed of lamellar-structured γ/α2 fine grains and fine equiaxed γ grains (duplex-like region), and another is composed of coarser equiaxed γ phase grains which form a chain perpendicular to the building direction (γ band region). In the γ bands, the α2 phase is hardly observed. The average layer thickness of the duplex-like region and the γ band was approximately 60 μm and 30 μm, respectively. The sum of these layer thicknesses corresponds approximately to the average thickness of powder layer fed at each cycle. The average grain size in the duplex-like region (including lamellar and γ grains) is about 11 μm, and in the γ bands about 20 μm. The lamellar thickness: γ lamellae average 162 nm, α2 lamellae average 48 nm. Cracks and residual pores are rarely observed; total porosity less than 0.5%.",
          "simplified": "Unique layered microstructure: alternating duplex-like regions (fine γ/α2 lamellae and equiaxed γ grains) and γ bands (coarser equiaxed γ grains, no α2). Layers perpendicular to building direction. Duplex-like region thickness ~60 μm, γ band thickness ~30 μm. Grain size: duplex-like ~11 μm, γ bands ~20 μm. Lamellar thickness: γ 162 nm, α2 48 nm. Porosity <0.5%."
        },
        "Main_Phase": "Gamma (γ)-TiAl",
